<article id="post-48911" class="post-48911 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-asides entry">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://ma.tt/2019/01/thirty-five/" rel="bookmark">Thirty-Five</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
		<figure class="post-thumbnail">
			<a class="post-thumbnail-inner" href="https://ma.tt/2019/01/thirty-five/" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1">
				<img width="1568" height="972" src="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?fit=1568%2C972&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=195%2C121&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=840%2C521&amp;ssl=1 840w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=768%2C476&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=1024%2C635&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=1568%2C972&amp;ssl=1 1568w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?w=1280 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 34.9rem) calc(100vw - 2rem), (max-width: 53rem) calc(8 * (100vw / 12)), (min-width: 53rem) calc(6 * (100vw / 12)), 100vw" data-attachment-id="48914" data-permalink="https://ma.tt/2019/01/thirty-five/tonga-wanderings-2-of-5/" data-orig-file="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?fit=1600%2C992&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1600,992" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;DSC-RX100M5&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1533339890&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;8.8&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;125&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.005&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Tonga &#8211; Wanderings &#8211; 2 of 5" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?fit=840%2C521&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?fit=640%2C397&amp;ssl=1" />			</a>
		</figure>

			
	<div class="entry-content">
		
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright is-resized"><img data-attachment-id="48912" data-permalink="https://ma.tt/2019/01/thirty-five/img_8762/" data-orig-file="https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?fit=3024%2C4032&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="3024,4032" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2.4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;iPhone X&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1546614517&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;6&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;80&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.02&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="IMG_8762" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?fit=555%2C740&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?fit=640%2C853&amp;ssl=1" src="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762-768x1024.jpg?resize=247%2C329&#038;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-48912" width="247" height="329" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?resize=768%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?resize=158%2C210&amp;ssl=1 158w, https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?resize=555%2C740&amp;ssl=1 555w, https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?resize=1568%2C2091&amp;ssl=1 1568w, https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?w=1280 1280w, https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/IMG_8762.jpg?w=1920 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 247px) 100vw, 247px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></figure></div>



<p>What a year.</p>



<p>First, it feels amazing to write this inside of the new Gutenberg block editor in WordPress 5.0. It was a labor of love for so many and the next chapters are going to be even more exciting.</p>



<p>The best part of the last year was growing closer to my friends and loved ones â&nbsp;I don&#8217;t know if it&#8217;s externally perceptible but my heart feels a lot more open. </p>



<p>I&#8217;ve found a good balance with meditation, work, sleep, fasting, eating, and reading that gives me a lot of joy, energy, and feels like a combination I could sustain the rest of my life.</p>



<p>Reading in particular was a highlight as I finished 38 books, which is the most in a year since I started tracking, and so many of them were truly excellent I&#8217;m going to do another post just on books. I will give a special call out to <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00TBKYK60/">The Paper Menagerie by Ken Liu</a>. Leaving my Kindle Oasis at an airport ended up being a blessing in disguise as I started using the Kindle app on my iPhone a lot more and that&#8217;s become my new favorite habit. (And the physical Kindle was returned!)</p>



<p>It was a strong travel year, covering 126 cities, 20 countries, and 377k miles. I especially enjoyed visits to Tulum, Iceland, Bodrum, Tonga, Kauai, Lanai, and Courchevel. I finally checked off my bucket list item to become scuba certified and had an amazing opportunity to swim with humpback whales.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide"><img data-attachment-id="48914" data-permalink="https://ma.tt/2019/01/thirty-five/tonga-wanderings-2-of-5/" data-orig-file="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?fit=1600%2C992&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1600,992" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;DSC-RX100M5&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1533339890&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;8.8&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;125&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.005&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Tonga &#8211; Wanderings &#8211; 2 of 5" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?fit=840%2C521&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?fit=640%2C397&amp;ssl=1" src="https://i1.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5-1024x635.jpg?resize=640%2C397&#038;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-48914" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=1024%2C635&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=195%2C121&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=840%2C521&amp;ssl=1 840w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=768%2C476&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?resize=1568%2C972&amp;ssl=1 1568w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w, https://i2.wp.com/ma.tt/files/2019/01/Tonga-Wanderings-2-of-5.jpg?w=1280 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /><figcaption>I was a few feet from <a href="https://www.comewander.com/">Adam Gazzaley when he took this photo</a>.</figcaption></figure>



<p>I also had lots of opportunities to practice patience, weathered a torrent of personally-directed criticism across every medium, and had a few months that were the hardest I&#8217;ve worked in my career. With the benefit of a little distance, though, those things don&#8217;t loom as large. I learned a ton â&nbsp;often the hard way but often that&#8217;s what it takes â&nbsp;and discovered I had some additional gears that can kick in when needed.</p>



<p>As I pass solidly into my mid-thirties, I don&#8217;t have any drastic shifts on the horizon but I am looking forward to continuing to strengthen the habits I&#8217;ve been able to develop this past year.</p>



<p>Other years: <a href="https://ma.tt/2003/01/bday/">19</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2004/01/so-im-20/">20</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2005/01/hot-barely-legal-matt/">21</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2006/01/matt-22/">22</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2007/01/twenty-three/">23</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2008/01/twenty-four/">24</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2009/01/twenty-five/">25</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2010/01/twenty-six/">26</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2011/01/twenty-seven/">27</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2012/01/twenty-eight/">28</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2013/01/twenty-nine/">29</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2014/01/matt-3-0/">30</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2015/01/thirty-one/">31</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2016/01/thirty-two/">32</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2017/01/thirty-three/">33</a>, <a href="https://ma.tt/2018/01/thirty-four/">34</a>, 35.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

